{"key":"post-12539242","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12539242</id>\n<content>When you shake your jars, you want to separate every kernel of grain from every other one.&amp;nbsp; Bang it on a fully inflated tire, or phone book, etc.&amp;nbsp; If it fails to recover, then it was contaminated with bacteria anyway.&amp;nbsp; Only shake once at around 20% to 30%.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Be careful using any lime but hydrated lime for a casing layer.&amp;nbsp; If it comes from dolomite limestone, it can negatively impact fruiting performance due to high Mg.&amp;nbsp; You can use calcium carbonate(ground limestone or oyster shells), but it's only so effective because it needs a month or two to break down, and most casing layers are finished by then.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12539365</next>\n<prev>12539186</prev>\n<first>12539186</first>\n<last>12542091</last>\n<when>1273540649</when>\n<utime>05/11/10 04:17 AM</utime>\n</post>"}